With the Custom filter, you can change the brightness values of each pixel in the image according to a predefined mathematical operation known as convolution (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kernel_(image_processing)). Each pixel is reassigned a value based on the values of surrounding pixels.

An analogue of the filter of the same name from Pixlr.
It is available in two versions: the first one works on Photopea scripts, the second one is implemented on WASM technology.
The second version is faster than the first, but in some cases it may show interpolation artifacts.
Styling a 3D histogram based on different image color parameters
Implemented various edge search algorithms: Kirsch, Laplace (3 x 3), Laplace (5 x 5), Prewitt, Roberts, Robinson, Scharr and Sobel
